til` pair can never match any instant and is refused with the EXISTING typed `InvalidArgument`/`InvalidArgumentError`; a non-integer bound is refused with the EXISTING `WriteValidation`/`WriteValidationError`. No new error type is minted. recovery_denylist UNCHANGED — still exactly the five REQ-054 names; neither field name collides with `recover`/`restore`/`repair`/`fix`/`rebuild`, so AC-041 is unaffected and was re-run green. Gated by requirement id + TDD test name (engine `slice15b_node_validity_write.rs`, TS `slice15b-node-validity-write.test.ts`, Py `test_slice15b_node_validity_write.py`) rather than by minting a new AC — AC-079 remains UNMINTED. This entry is a PROPOSAL recorded so the branch is not red; the orchestrator is escalating it for sign-off. ***0.8.20 Slice 15d (R-20-PR / R-20-EAV, projection registry + EAV/property-FTS) — AWAITING HITL SIGN-OFF, NOT SIGNED.*** This delta adds TWO net-new governed commands: `configure_projections`/`configureProjections` (Engine.configure_projections in Python, Engine.configureProjections in TypeScript) — the declarative, idempotent projection-registry apply (C-1: the engine is the SOLE projection authority; explicit `drop`, destructive-change refusal, graceful-deferred `rankable`/`searchable→vector`) — and `read.projections` (a single name in BOTH bindings: Python `fathomdb.read.projections`, TypeScript `read.projections` — the registry introspection folded into the `read.*` namespace, C5). The delta ALSO carries the non-command types `ProjectionSpec` / `ProjectionDelta` / `ProjectionRole` (Py `fathomdb.types.*` + native `fathomdb._fathomdb.*`, TS exports; the `ProjectionSpec.vector` sub-object is where Slice 20's `dense_readiness` attaches additively) and one net-new typed error, `ProjectionDestructiveError` (Py `fathomdb.errors.ProjectionDestructiveError` carrying `name`/`delta`, TS `ProjectionDestructiveError` mapped from the `FDB_PROJECTION_DESTRUCTIVE` envelope). recovery_denylist UNCHANGED — still exactly the f