 // The operator-seam report types (`dev/interfaces/rust.md` § 2b) — CLI-only,

codex
The projection registry mostly compiles and targeted tests pass, but the new same-transaction attribute projection ignores lifecycle visibility for pending nodes. This can expose rows that the canonical read model intentionally hides.

Review comment:

- [P2] Gate attribute projection on active lifecycle state — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15d/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:15227-15228
  When a projection is already declared and a caller writes a node with `InitialState::Pending`, this unconditional projection writes its values into `canonical_attributes` / `property_search_index` even though the backfill path only includes `state = 'active'` rows and normal reads exclude pending nodes. That makes same-session property filters/FTS over the new tables see quarantined content until a boot re-derive or reconfigure clears it; pass the node state through and only project active rows, with lifecycle transitions maintaining these rows.
